[{"id":"VR005365","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Beams of monochromatic light are emitted from two sources. Light from source <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Α</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> has half the wavelength of light from source <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Β</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>. Which of the following correctly compares the energy <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"E\"><math alttext=\"E\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>E</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> of photons emitted by <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>A</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> to the energy of photons emitted by <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>B</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> and includes a correct justification?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR005365_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"E sub A equals 2 E sub B\"><math alttext=\"E sub A equals 2 E sub B\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>E</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Α</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><msub><mrow><mi>E</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Β</mi></mrow></msub></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>, because the energy of photons is inversely proportional to the wavelength of the light.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"E sub A equals one half E sub B\"><math alttext=\"E sub A equals one half E sub B\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>E</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Α</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac><msub><mrow><mi>E</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Β</mi></mrow></msub></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>, because the energy of photons is proportional to the wavelength of the light.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"E sub A equals E sub B\"><math alttext=\"E sub A equals E sub B\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>E</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Α</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mrow><mi>E</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Β</mi></mrow></msub></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>, because the energy of photons, like the speed of light, is independent of their wavelength.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"E sub A equals one quarter E sub B\"><math alttext=\"E sub A equals one quarter E sub B\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>E</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Α</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>4</mn></mrow></mfrac><msub><mrow><mi>E</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Β</mi></mrow></msub></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>, because the energy of photons is inversely proportional to the square of the wavelength.</p>"],"answer":0}]